Type called "GlobalOptimizationOptions":
    population_size as Integer
    max_generations as Integer
    mutation_factor as Float
    crossover_probability as Float
    tolerance_diversity as Float
    selection_pressure as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Process called "backtracking_line_search" that takes func as Function[NDArray.NDArray, Float] and x as NDArray.NDArray and direction as NDArray.NDArray and grad as NDArray.NDArray and f_current as Float returns LineSearchResult:
    Let c1 be 1e-4
    Let rho be 0.5
    Let alpha be 1.0
    Let max_iter be 50
    Let n_iter be 0
    Let grad_dot_dir be vector_dot_product with a as grad and b as direction
    While n_iter < max_iter:
        Let x_new be vector_add with a as x and b as vector_scale with vector as direction and scalar as alpha
        Let f_new be func with x_new
        Note: Armijo condition
        Let armijo_rhs be f_current + c1 * alpha * grad_dot_dir
        If f_new <= armijo_rhs:
            Return LineSearchResult with:
                step_size as alpha
                function_value as f_new
                gradient_dot_direction as grad_dot_dir
                n_function_evaluations as n_iter + 1
                success as true
                termination_condition as "Armijo satisfied"
                metadata as dictionary containing
        Set alpha to alpha * rho
        Set n_iter to n_iter + 1
    Return LineSearchResult with:
        step_size as alpha
        function_value as f_current
        gradient_dot_direction as grad_dot_dir
        n_function_evaluations as n_iter
        success as false
        termination_condition as "Maximum iterations exceeded"
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "compute_finite_difference_gradient" that takes func as Function[NDArray.NDArray, Float] and x as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let h be 1e-8
    Let n_vars be x.size
    Let gradient be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing n_vars
    Let f_x be func with x
    For i from 0 to n_vars - 1:
        Let x_plus_h be NDArray.copy_array with arr as x
        Set x_plus_h.data at index i to x_plus_h.data at index i + h
        Let f_plus_h be func with x_plus_h
        Let derivative be (f_plus_h - f_x) / h
        Set gradient.data at index i to derivative
    Return gradient

Note: Vector and matrix operations
Process called "vector_add" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and b as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Return NDArray.add with a as a and b as b

Process called "vector_subtract" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and b as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let result be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing a.size
    For i from 0 to a.size - 1:
        Set result.data at index i to a.data at index i - b.data at index i
    Return result

Process called "vector_scale" that takes vector as NDArray.NDArray and scalar as Float returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let result be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing vector.size
    For i from 0 to vector.size - 1:
        Set result.data at index i to vector.data at index i * scalar
    Return result

Process called "negate_vector" that takes vector as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Return vector_scale with vector as vector and scalar as -1.0

Process called "vector_dot_product" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and b as NDArray.NDArray returns Float:
    Let result be 0.0
    For i from 0 to a.size - 1:
        Set result to result + a.data at index i * b.data at index i
    Return result

Process called "euclidean_distance" that takes a as NDArray.NDArray and b as NDArray.NDArray returns Float:
    Let sum_sq_diff be 0.0
    For i from 0 to a.size - 1:
        Let a_val be Float.from with value as a.data at index i
        Let b_val be Float.from with value as b.data at index i
        Let diff be a_val - b_val
        Set sum_sq_diff to sum_sq_diff + diff * diff
    Return Math.sqrt with x as sum_sq_diff

Process called "calculate_vector_norm" that takes vector as NDArray.NDArray returns Float:
    Let sum_squares be 0.0
    For i from 0 to vector.size - 1:
        Let val be Float.from with value as vector.data at index i
        Set sum_squares to sum_squares + val * val
    Return Math.sqrt with x as sum_squares

Process called "create_identity_matrix" that takes size as Integer returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let matrix be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing size, size
    For i from 0 to size - 1:
        Set matrix.data at index (i * size + i) to 1.0
    Return matrix

Process called "matrix_vector_multiply" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray and vector as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let n_rows be matrix.shape at index 0
    Let n_cols be matrix.shape at index 1
    Let result be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing n_rows
    For i from 0 to n_rows - 1:
        Let sum be 0.0
        For j from 0 to n_cols - 1:
            Let matrix_val be Float.from with value as matrix.data at index (i * n_cols + j)
            Let vector_val be Float.from with value as vector.data at index j
            Set sum to sum + matrix_val * vector_val
        Set result.data at index i to sum
    Return result

Process called "matrix_multiply" that takes A as NDArray.NDArray and B as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let rows_A be A.shape at index 0
    Let cols_A be A.shape at index 1
    Let cols_B be B.shape at index 1
    Let result be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing rows_A, cols_B
    For i from 0 to rows_A - 1:
        For j from 0 to cols_B - 1:
            Let sum be 0.0
            For k from 0 to cols_A - 1:
                Let a_ik be Float.from with value as A.data at index (i * cols_A + k)
                Let b_kj be Float.from with value as B.data at index (k * cols_B + j)
                Set sum to sum + a_ik * b_kj
            Set result.data at index (i * cols_B + j) to sum
    Return result

Note: BFGS update
Process called "update_bfgs_hessian" that takes hessian_inv as NDArray.NDArray and s as NDArray.NDArray and y as NDArray.NDArray:
    Note: Full BFGS update: H_{k+1} = (I - ρ*s*y^T)*H_k*(I - ρ*y*s^T) + ρ*s*s^T
    Let s_dot_y be vector_dot_product with a as s and b as y
    If Math.abs with x as s_dot_y < 1e-10:
        Return
    Let n be s.size
    Let rho be 1.0 / s_dot_y
    
    Note: Create intermediate matrices
    Let I_rho_sy = create_identity_matrix with size as n
    Let I_rho_ys = create_identity_matrix with size as n
    
    Note: I - ρ*s*y^T
    For i from 0 to n - 1:
        For j from 0 to n - 1:
            Let s_i be Float.from with value as s.data at index i
            Let y_j be Float.from with value as y.data at index j
            Let current_val be Float.from with value as I_rho_sy.data at index (i * n + j)
            Set I_rho_sy.data at index (i * n + j) to current_val - rho * s_i * y_j
    
    Note: I - ρ*y*s^T  
    For i from 0 to n - 1:
        For j from 0 to n - 1:
            Let y_i be Float.from with value as y.data at index i
            Let s_j be Float.from with value as s.data at index j
            Let current_val be Float.from with value as I_rho_ys.data at index (i * n + j)
            Set I_rho_ys.data at index (i * n + j) to current_val - rho * y_i * s_j
    
    Note: Compute (I - ρ*s*y^T)*H_k
    Let temp_matrix be matrix_multiply with A as I_rho_sy and B as hessian_inv
    
    Note: Compute ((I - ρ*s*y^T)*H_k)*(I - ρ*y*s^T)
    Let updated_hessian be matrix_multiply with A as temp_matrix and B as I_rho_ys
    
    Note: Add ρ*s*s^T term
    For i from 0 to n - 1:
        For j from 0 to n - 1:
            Let s_i be Float.from with value as s.data at index i
            Let s_j be Float.from with value as s.data at index j
            Let current_val be Float.from with value as updated_hessian.data at index (i * n + j)
            Set updated_hessian.data at index (i * n + j) to current_val + rho * s_i * s_j
    
    Note: Copy result back to hessian_inv
    For i from 0 to n - 1:
        For j from 0 to n - 1:
            Set hessian_inv.data at index (i * n + j) to updated_hessian.data at index (i * n + j)

Note: Result constructors
Process called "create_success_result" that takes x as NDArray.NDArray and fun as Float and iterations as Integer and func_evals as Integer and grad_evals as Integer and grad_norm as Float and time as Float returns OptimizationResult:
    Return OptimizationResult with:
        x as x
        fun as fun
        success as true
        message as "Optimization terminated successfully"
        n_iterations as iterations
        n_function_evaluations as func_evals
        n_gradient_evaluations as grad_evals
        n_hessian_evaluations as 0
        final_gradient_norm as grad_norm
        step_size as 0.0
        convergence_criteria as create_default_convergence_criteria()
        optimization_time as time
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "create_failure_result" that takes x as NDArray.NDArray and fun as Float and message as String and iterations as Integer and func_evals as Integer and time as Float returns OptimizationResult:
    Return OptimizationResult with:
        x as x
        fun as fun
        success as false
        message as message
        n_iterations as iterations
        n_function_evaluations as func_evals
        n_gradient_evaluations as 0
        n_hessian_evaluations as 0
        final_gradient_norm as 0.0
        step_size as 0.0
        convergence_criteria as create_default_convergence_criteria()
        optimization_time as time
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "create_default_convergence_criteria" returns ConvergenceCriteria:
    Return ConvergenceCriteria with:
        tolerance_fun as 1e-8
        tolerance_grad as 1e-6
        tolerance_x as 1e-8
        max_iterations as 1000
        max_function_evaluations as 10000
        check_gradient as true
        check_step_size as false
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "create_initial_simplex" that takes x0 as NDArray.NDArray returns List[NDArray.NDArray]:
    Note: Create proper Nelder-Mead simplex with adaptive step sizes
    Let n_vars be x0.size
    Let simplex be list containing
    Add NDArray.copy_array with arr as x0 to simplex
    
    For i from 0 to n_vars - 1:
        Let vertex be NDArray.copy_array with arr as x0
        Let x_i = Float.from with value as x0.data at index i
        
        Note: Use adaptive step size based on magnitude of x_i
        Let step_size be if Math.abs with x as x_i > 1e-6 then Math.abs with x as x_i * 0.05 otherwise 0.00025
        
        Note: Ensure step size is reasonable
        Set step_size to Math.max with a as step_size and b as 1e-4
        Set step_size to Math.min with a as step_size and b as 1.0
        
        Set vertex.data at index i to x_i + step_size
        Add vertex to simplex
    Return simplex

Process called "evaluate_simplex" that takes simplex as List[NDArray.NDArray] and func as Function[NDArray.NDArray, Float] returns List[Float]:
    Let values be list containing
    For each vertex in simplex:
        Add func with vertex to values
    Return values

Process called "sort_simplex" that takes simplex as List[NDArray.NDArray] and values as List[Float]:
    Note: Simple bubble sort
    Let n be Collections.List.length with lst as simplex
    For i from 0 to n - 2:
        For j from 0 to n - 2 - i:
            If values at index j > values at index (j + 1):
                Let temp_vertex be simplex at index j
                Set simplex at index j to simplex at index (j + 1)
                Set simplex at index (j + 1) to temp_vertex
                Let temp_value be values at index j
                Set values at index j to values at index (j + 1)
                Set values at index (j + 1) to temp_value

Process called "compute_simplex_centroid" that takes simplex as List[NDArray.NDArray] and n_points as Integer returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let first_vertex be simplex at index 0
    Let centroid be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing first_vertex.size
    For i from 0 to n_points - 1:
        Let vertex be simplex at index i
        For j from 0 to vertex.size - 1:
            Set centroid.data at index j to centroid.data at index j + vertex.data at index j
    For j from 0 to centroid.size - 1:
        Set centroid.data at index j to centroid.data at index j / Float.from with value as n_points
    Return centroid

Process called "reflect_point" that takes point as NDArray.NDArray and centroid as NDArray.NDArray and alpha as Float returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let direction be vector_subtract with a as centroid and b as point
    Return vector_add with a as centroid and b as vector_scale with vector as direction and scalar as alpha

Process called "shrink_simplex" that takes simplex as List[NDArray.NDArray] and values as List[Float] and func as Function[NDArray.NDArray, Float]:
    Let best_vertex be simplex at index 0
    For i from 1 to Collections.List.length with lst as simplex - 1:
        Let vertex be simplex at index i
        Let shrunk_vertex be vector_add with a as best_vertex and b as vector_scale with vector as vector_subtract with a as vertex and b as best_vertex and scalar as 0.5
        Set simplex at index i to shrunk_vertex
        Set values at index i to func with shrunk_vertex

Note: Root finding result type
Type called "RootResult":
    root as Float
    function_value as Float
    iterations as Integer
    converged as Boolean
    method as String
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Process called "create_root_success" that takes root as Float and function_value as Float and iterations as Integer returns RootResult:
    Return RootResult with:
        root as root
        function_value as function_value
        iterations as iterations
        converged as true
        method as "Brent"
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "create_root_failure" that takes message as String returns RootResult:
    Return RootResult with:
        root as 0.0
        function_value as 0.0
        iterations as 0
        converged as false
        method as "Failed"
        metadata as dictionary containing "error" and message

Process called "evaluate_constraints" that takes constraints as List[ConstraintFunction] and x as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let n_constraints be Collections.List.length with lst as constraints
    Let values be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing n_constraints
    For i from 0 to n_constraints - 1:
        Let constraint be constraints at index i
        Set values.data at index i to constraint.function with x
    Return values

Process called "evaluate_constraint_gradients" that takes constraints as List[ConstraintFunction] and x as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let n_constraints be Collections.List.length with lst as constraints
    Let n_vars be x.size
    Let gradients be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing n_constraints, n_vars
    For i from 0 to n_constraints - 1:
        Let constraint be constraints at index i
        Let grad be if constraint.gradient is not None then constraint.gradient with x otherwise compute_finite_difference_gradient with func as constraint.function and x as x
        For j from 0 to n_vars - 1:
            Set gradients.data at index (i * n_vars + j) to grad.data at index j
    Return gradients

Process called "compute_kkt_residual" that takes grad_f as NDArray.NDArray and constraint_gradients as NDArray.NDArray and multipliers as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Note: KKT residual: ∇f + ∑λᵢ∇gᵢ
    Let n_vars be grad_f.size
    Let n_constraints be multipliers.size
    Let residual be NDArray.copy_array with arr as grad_f
    For i from 0 to n_constraints - 1:
        Let lambda_i be Float.from with value as multipliers.data at index i
        For j from 0 to n_vars - 1:
            Let grad_constraint_ij be Float.from with value as constraint_gradients.data at index (i * n_vars + j)
            Let current_residual be Float.from with value as residual.data at index j
            Set residual.data at index j to current_residual + lambda_i * grad_constraint_ij
    Return residual

Process called "calculate_constraint_violation" that takes values as NDArray.NDArray returns Float:
    Let max_violation be 0.0
    For i from 0 to values.size - 1:
        Let violation be Math.max with a as 0.0 and b as Float.from with value as values.data at index i
        Set max_violation to Math.max with a as max_violation and b as violation
    Return max_violation

Process called "approximate_hessian_bfgs" that takes x as NDArray.NDArray and n as Integer returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Note: Initial Hessian approximation for BFGS - use scaled identity
    Note: In full BFGS, this would be updated using: H_{k+1} = H_k + (s_k s_k^T)/(s_k^T y_k) - (H_k y_k y_k^T H_k)/(y_k^T H_k y_k)
    Let hessian be create_identity_matrix with size as n
    Note: Scale diagonal based on problem characteristics
    Let typical_scale be 1.0
    For i from 0 to n - 1:
        Set hessian.data at index (i * n + i) to typical_scale
    Return hessian

Process called "solve_quadratic_subproblem" that takes hessian as NDArray.NDArray and grad as NDArray.NDArray and constraints as NDArray.NDArray and constraint_values as NDArray.NDArray returns QPSolution:
    Note: Solve QP: min 0.5*p^T*H*p + g^T*p subject to A*p + c = 0
    Let n_vars be grad.size
    Let n_constraints be constraint_values.size
    
    If n_constraints equals 0:
        Note: Unconstrained case: H*p = -g
        Let direction be solve_linear_system with A as hessian and b as negate_vector with vector as grad
        Return QPSolution with:
            direction as direction
            multipliers as NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing 0
            success as true
    
    Note: Constrained case: solve KKT system [H A^T; A 0] * [p; lambda] = [-g; -c]
    Let kkt_size be n_vars + n_constraints
    Let kkt_matrix be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing kkt_size, kkt_size
    Let kkt_rhs be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing kkt_size
    
    Note: Fill KKT matrix: [H A^T; A 0]
    For i from 0 to n_vars - 1:
        For j from 0 to n_vars - 1:
            Set kkt_matrix.data at index (i * kkt_size + j) to hessian.data at index (i * n_vars + j)
        Set kkt_rhs.data at index i to negative grad.data at index i
    
    For i from 0 to n_constraints - 1:
        For j from 0 to n_vars - 1:
            Let constraint_grad = constraints.data at index (i * n_vars + j)
            Set kkt_matrix.data at index (i * kkt_size + (n_vars + j)) to constraint_grad
            Set kkt_matrix.data at index ((n_vars + i) * kkt_size + j) to constraint_grad
        Set kkt_rhs.data at index (n_vars + i) to negative constraint_values.data at index i
    
    Note: Solve KKT system
    Let kkt_solution be solve_linear_system with A as kkt_matrix and b as kkt_rhs
    
    Note: Extract direction and multipliers
    Let direction be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing n_vars
    Let multipliers be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing n_constraints
    
    For i from 0 to n_vars - 1:
        Set direction.data at index i to kkt_solution.data at index i
    
    For i from 0 to n_constraints - 1:
        Set multipliers.data at index i to kkt_solution.data at index (n_vars + i)
    
    Return QPSolution with:
        direction as direction
        multipliers as multipliers
        success as true

Type called "QPSolution":
    direction as NDArray.NDArray
    multipliers as NDArray.NDArray
    success as Boolean

Process called "create_merit_function" that takes objective as ObjectiveFunction and constraints as List[ConstraintFunction] and penalty as Float returns Function[NDArray.NDArray, Float]:
    Return function that takes x as NDArray.NDArray returns Float:
        Let objective_value be objective.function with x
        Let penalty_sum be 0.0
        For each constraint in constraints:
            Let violation be Math.max with a as 0.0 and b as constraint.function with x
            Set penalty_sum to penalty_sum + violation * violation
        Return objective_value + penalty * penalty_sum

Process called "initialize_random_population" that takes bounds as List[Tuple[Float, Float]] and size as Integer returns List[NDArray.NDArray]:
    Let population be list containing
    Let n_vars be Collections.List.length with lst as bounds
    Let rng be Math.create_random_state with seed as 42
    For i from 0 to size - 1:
        Let individual be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing n_vars
        For j from 0 to n_vars - 1:
            Let bound be bounds at index j
            Let lower be bound.first
            Let upper be bound.second
            Let random_val be Math.random_uniform with rng as rng
            Let value be lower + random_val * (upper - lower)
            Set individual.data at index j to value
        Add individual to population
    Return population

Process called "evaluate_population" that takes population as List[NDArray.NDArray] and func as Function[NDArray.NDArray, Float] returns List[Float]:
    Let fitness be list containing
    For each individual in population:
        Add func with individual to fitness
    Return fitness

Process called "get_best_individual" that takes population as List[NDArray.NDArray] and fitness as List[Float] returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let best_index be 0
    Let best_fitness be fitness at index 0
    For i from 1 to Collections.List.length with lst as fitness - 1:
        If fitness at index i < best_fitness:
            Set best_index to i
            Set best_fitness to fitness at index i
    Return population at index best_index

Process called "get_best_fitness" that takes fitness as List[Float] returns Float:
    Let best be fitness at index 0
    For each f in fitness:
        Set best to Math.min with a as best and b as f
    Return best

Process called "create_mutant_vector" that takes population as List[NDArray.NDArray] and target_index as Integer and F as Float returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let pop_size be Collections.List.length with lst as population
    Let n_vars be (population at index 0).size
    Note: DE/rand/1 strategy: V = X_r1 + F * (X_r2 - X_r3)
    Note: Select three random distinct indices different from target_index
    Let r1 be (target_index + 1) % pop_size
    Let r2 be (target_index + 2) % pop_size
    Let r3 be (target_index + 3) % pop_size
    Note: Ensure all indices are distinct
    If r2 equals r1:
        Set r2 to (r2 + 1) % pop_size
    If r3 equals r1 or r3 equals r2:
        Set r3 to (r3 + 1) % pop_size
    Let x_r1 be population at index r1
    Let x_r2 be population at index r2
    Let x_r3 be population at index r3
    Let mutant be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing n_vars
    For i from 0 to n_vars - 1:
        Let val_r1 be Float.from with value as x_r1.data at index i
        Let val_r2 be Float.from with value as x_r2.data at index i
        Let val_r3 be Float.from with value as x_r3.data at index i
        Set mutant.data at index i to val_r1 + F * (val_r2 - val_r3)
    Return mutant

Process called "crossover_vectors" that takes target as NDArray.NDArray and mutant as NDArray.NDArray and CR as Float returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let trial be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing target.size
    Let rng be Math.create_random_state with seed as 123
    Note: Ensure at least one parameter is inherited from mutant vector
    Let j_rand be Math.random_int with rng as rng and min_val as 0 and max_val as target.size - 1
    For i from 0 to target.size - 1:
        Let rand_val be Math.random_uniform with rng as rng
        If rand_val < CR or i equals j_rand:
            Set trial.data at index i to mutant.data at index i
        Otherwise:
            Set trial.data at index i to target.data at index i
    Return trial

Process called "apply_bounds_to_vector" that takes vector as NDArray.NDArray and bounds as List[Tuple[Float, Float]] returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let bounded_vector be NDArray.copy_array with arr as vector
    For i from 0 to vector.size - 1:
        Let bound be bounds at index i
        Let value be Float.from with value as vector.data at index i
        Let clamped_value be Math.max with a as bound.first and b as Math.min with a as bound.second and b as value
        Set bounded_vector.data at index i to clamped_value
    Return bounded_vector

Process called "calculate_population_diversity" that takes population as List[NDArray.NDArray] returns Float:
    Note: Calculate average pairwise Euclidean distance as diversity metric
    Let pop_size be Collections.List.length with lst as population
    If pop_size < 2:
        Return 0.0
    Let total_distance be 0.0
    Let num_pairs be 0
    For i from 0 to pop_size - 2:
        For j from i + 1 to pop_size - 1:
            Let individual_i be population at index i
            Let individual_j be population at index j
            Let distance be euclidean_distance with a as individual_i and b as individual_j
            Set total_distance to total_distance + distance
            Set num_pairs to num_pairs + 1
    If num_pairs > 0:
        Return total_distance / Float.from with value as num_pairs
    Return 0.0

Process called "calculate_sum_of_squares" that takes residuals as NDArray.NDArray returns Float:
    Let sum_sq be 0.0
    For i from 0 to residuals.size - 1:
        Let r be Float.from with value as residuals.data at index i
        Set sum_sq to sum_sq + r * r
    Return sum_sq

Process called "compute_least_squares_gradient" that takes jacobian as NDArray.NDArray and residuals as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Note: J^T * r (gradient of 0.5 * ||r||^2)
    Let n_residuals be jacobian.shape at index 0
    Let n_vars be jacobian.shape at index 1
    Let gradient be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing n_vars
    For j from 0 to n_vars - 1:
        Let sum be 0.0
        For i from 0 to n_residuals - 1:
            Let jacobian_ij be Float.from with value as jacobian.data at index (i * n_vars + j)
            Let residual_i be Float.from with value as residuals.data at index i
            Set sum to sum + jacobian_ij * residual_i
        Set gradient.data at index j to sum
    Return gradient

Process called "compute_gauss_newton_hessian" that takes jacobian as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Note: J^T * J (Gauss-Newton approximation to Hessian)
    Let n_residuals be jacobian.shape at index 0
    Let n_vars be jacobian.shape at index 1
    Let hessian be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing n_vars, n_vars
    For i from 0 to n_vars - 1:
        For j from 0 to n_vars - 1:
            Let sum be 0.0
            For k from 0 to n_residuals - 1:
                Let j_ki be Float.from with value as jacobian.data at index (k * n_vars + i)
                Let j_kj be Float.from with value as jacobian.data at index (k * n_vars + j)
                Set sum to sum + j_ki * j_kj
            Set hessian.data at index (i * n_vars + j) to sum
    Return hessian

Process called "add_diagonal_damping" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray and damping as Float returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let augmented be NDArray.copy_array with arr as matrix
    Let n be matrix.shape at index 0
    For i from 0 to n - 1:
        Let current_val be Float.from with value as augmented.data at index (i * n + i)
        Set augmented.data at index (i * n + i) to current_val + damping
    Return augmented

Process called "solve_linear_system" that takes A as NDArray.NDArray and b as NDArray.NDArray returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Note: LU decomposition with partial pivoting for solving Ax = b
    Let n be A.shape at index 0
    Let L be create_identity_matrix with size as n
    Let U be NDArray.copy_array with arr as A
    Let P be create_identity_matrix with size as n
    Let x be NDArray.copy_array with arr as b
    
    Note: LU decomposition with partial pivoting
    For k from 0 to n - 2:
        Note: Find pivot
        Let max_val be Math.abs with x as U.data at index (k * n + k)
        Let pivot_row be k
        For i from k + 1 to n - 1:
            Let current_val be Math.abs with x as U.data at index (i * n + k)
            If current_val > max_val:
                Set max_val to current_val
                Set pivot_row to i
        
        Note: Swap rows if needed
        If pivot_row != k:
            Call swap_matrix_rows with matrix as U and row1 as k and row2 as pivot_row
            Call swap_matrix_rows with matrix as P and row1 as k and row2 as pivot_row
            Call swap_vector_elements with vector as x and i as k and j as pivot_row
        
        Note: Gaussian elimination
        For i from k + 1 to n - 1:
            Let factor be U.data at index (i * n + k) / U.data at index (k * n + k)
            Set L.data at index (i * n + k) to factor
            For j from k to n - 1:
                Let u_ij be Float.from with value as U.data at index (i * n + j)
                Let u_kj be Float.from with value as U.data at index (k * n + j)
                Set U.data at index (i * n + j) to u_ij - factor * u_kj
    
    Note: Forward substitution (Ly = Pb)
    For i from 0 to n - 1:
        Let sum be 0.0
        For j from 0 to i - 1:
            Let l_ij be Float.from with value as L.data at index (i * n + j)
            Let x_j be Float.from with value as x.data at index j
            Set sum to sum + l_ij * x_j
        Let x_i be Float.from with value as x.data at index i
        Set x.data at index i to x_i - sum
    
    Note: Back substitution (Ux = y)
    For i from n - 1 down to 0:
        Let sum be 0.0
        For j from i + 1 to n - 1:
            Let u_ij be Float.from with value as U.data at index (i * n + j)
            Let x_j be Float.from with value as x.data at index j
            Set sum to sum + u_ij * x_j
        Let x_i be Float.from with value as x.data at index i
        Let u_ii be Float.from with value as U.data at index (i * n + i)
        Set x.data at index i to (x_i - sum) / u_ii
    
    Return x

Process called "compute_predicted_reduction" that takes gradient as NDArray.NDArray and hessian as NDArray.NDArray and step as NDArray.NDArray returns Float:
    Note: Predicted reduction: -g^T*p - 0.5*p^T*H*p (negative because we want reduction)
    Let grad_dot_step be vector_dot_product with a as gradient and b as step
    Let hessian_step be matrix_vector_multiply with matrix as hessian and vector as step
    Let step_hessian_step be vector_dot_product with a as step and b as hessian_step
    Return negative grad_dot_step - 0.5 * step_hessian_step

Note: Helper functions for linear algebra
Process called "swap_matrix_rows" that takes matrix as NDArray.NDArray and row1 as Integer and row2 as Integer:
    Let n_cols be matrix.shape at index 1
    For j from 0 to n_cols - 1:
        Let temp be matrix.data at index (row1 * n_cols + j)
        Set matrix.data at index (row1 * n_cols + j) to matrix.data at index (row2 * n_cols + j)
        Set matrix.data at index (row2 * n_cols + j) to temp

Process called "swap_vector_elements" that takes vector as NDArray.NDArray and i as Integer and j as Integer:
    Let temp be vector.data at index i
    Set vector.data at index i to vector.data at index j
    Set vector.data at index j to temp

Type called "Tuple":
    first as Float
    second as Float